<br>
Usually when i talk to you, in game or in forums, it is only a positive thing. You are all good people with spotless reputations. We at Tribulation consider you all to be &quot;allies&quot; at least in principal if not in actual guild policies. <br>
<br>
So, it is with a heavy heart that I bring a complaint to you. I have been most offended by someone coming into our house and spewing bile. In a recent post Kayla posted the following quote:<br>
<br>
&quot;arguing online is like competing in the special olympics.Even if you win, your still a retard.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now, this is patently offensive, rude, mean and just plain wrong. I am not talking about calling someone a &quot;retard&quot; I am talking about the attitude towards people with mental retardation. I cannot let this pass without comment. As the RL father of a child with mental retardation I take great personal offense to this comment. I hope this does not reflect the general attitude of CoS.<br>
<br>
Thank you for letting me vent.<br>
<br>
Borm, Guildleader of Tribulation<br>
<br>
<br>
ps - Kayla the contraction of &quot;you are&quot; is you're not your, but I am sure that you knew that. <br>
